(445,58,'service_description','<p>When your air conditioning system breaks down in South Florida, you need fast, reliable repair service from experienced HVAC professionals. At Sunnyside AC, our certified technicians have over 20 years of experience diagnosing and repairing all types of AC problems, from minor issues to major system failures.</p>\n\n<p>Our comprehensive AC repair services address all common air conditioning problems including refrigerant leaks, frozen evaporator coils, faulty compressors, electrical issues, thermostat malfunctions, clogged drain lines, and damaged fan motors. We service all major HVAC brands including Carrier, Trane, Lennox, Goodman, Rheem, York, American Standard, and more.</p>\n\n<p>We understand that AC problems don\'t wait for convenient times. That\'s why we offer same-day emergency repair service throughout South Florida. Our technicians arrive fully equipped with diagnostic tools and common replacement parts, allowing us to complete most repairs in a single visit.</p>\n\n<p>Every AC repair begins with a thorough diagnostic inspection using advanced testing equipment. We identify the root cause of the problemnot just the symptomsand provide you with upfront, transparent pricing before starting any work. Our technicians explain what\'s wrong, what options you have, and what we recommend based on your system\'s age and condition.</p>\n\n<p>All repairs are backed by our workmanship warranty and satisfaction guarantee. We use only high-quality OEM and approved aftermarket parts to ensure long-lasting repairs. Our goal is to restore your comfort quickly while helping you avoid costly future breakdowns through proper diagnosis and quality repairs.</p>'),
(446,58,'service_benefits','a:8:{i:0;a:1:{s:7:\"benefit\";s:42:\"24/7 Emergency AC Repair Service Available\";}i:1;a:1:{s:7:\"benefit\";s:45:\"Licensed, Insured & EPA Certified Technicians\";}i:2;a:1:{s:7:\"benefit\";s:41:\"Same-Day Service Throughout South Florida\";}i:3;a:1:{s:7:\"benefit\";s:45:\"Upfront Pricing - No Hidden Fees or Surprises\";}i:4;a:1:{s:7:\"benefit\";s:30:\"All Major HVAC Brands Serviced\";}i:5;a:1:{s:7:\"benefit\";s:49:\"Fully Stocked Service Vehicles for Faster Repairs\";}i:6;a:1:{s:7:\"benefit\";s:35:\"Workmanship Warranty on All Repairs\";}i:7;a:1:{s:7:\"benefit\";s:27:\"100% Satisfaction Guarantee\";}}'),
(447,58,'service_process','a:5:{i:0;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"Schedule Your Repair\";s:11:\"description\";s:100:\"Call us or book online. We offer same-day appointments and emergency service for urgent AC failures.\";}i:1;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:21:\"Diagnostic Inspection\";s:11:\"description\";s:122:\"Our certified technician thoroughly inspects your AC system using advanced diagnostic tools to identify the exact problem.\";}i:2;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"Transparent Pricing\";s:11:\"description\";s:113:\"We provide upfront pricing before any work begins. You\'ll know exactly what the repair costs with no hidden fees.\";}i:3;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:13:\"Expert Repair\";s:11:\"description\";s:119:\"Our technician completes the repair using quality parts and proven techniques. Most repairs are completed in one visit.\";}i:4;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:14:\"System Testing\";s:11:\"description\";s:113:\"We thoroughly test your AC system to ensure it\'s cooling efficiently and all components are functioning properly.\";}}'),
(448,58,'service_faqs','a:8:{i:0;a:2:{s:8:\"question\";s:33:\"How quickly can you repair my AC?\";s:6:\"answer\";s:206:\"We offer same-day service throughout South Florida. For emergencies, we can often arrive within 2 hours. Most repairs are completed during the first visit, typically taking 1-3 hours depending on the issue.\";}i:1;a:2:{s:8:\"question\";s:33:\"Do you offer emergency AC repair?\";s:6:\"answer\";s:200:\"Yes, we provide 24/7 emergency AC repair service. We understand that AC failures don\'t wait for business hours, especially during Florida\'s hot summer months. Call us anytime for immediate assistance.\";}i:2;a:2:{s:8:\"question\";s:40:\"What brands of AC systems do you repair?\";s:6:\"answer\";s:216:\"We repair all major HVAC brands including Carrier, Trane, Lennox, Goodman, Rheem, York, American Standard, Bryant, Daikin, Mitsubishi, and more. Our technicians are trained on both residential and commercial systems.\";}i:3;a:2:{s:8:\"question\";s:29:\"How much does AC repair cost?\";s:6:\"answer\";s:261:\"Repair costs vary depending on the issue. Simple fixes like thermostat replacement or capacitor replacement typically cost $150-$400, while major repairs like compressor replacement can cost $1,200-$2,500. We always provide upfront pricing before starting work.\";}i:4;a:2:{s:8:\"question\";s:38:\"Should I repair or replace my AC unit?\";s:6:\"answer\";s:273:\"This depends on your system\'s age, the repair cost, and efficiency. As a rule of thumb, if your AC is over 10 years old and the repair costs more than 50% of replacement, replacement may be more cost-effective. We\'ll give you honest recommendations based on your situation.\";}i:5;a:2:{s:8:\"question\";s:32:\"Do you warranty your AC repairs?\";s:6:\"answer\";s:158:\"Yes, all our repairs come with a workmanship warranty. Parts warranties vary by manufacturer, typically ranging from 1-5 years. We stand behind our work 100%.\";}i:6;a:2:{s:8:\"question\";s:41:\"What are common signs my AC needs repair?\";s:6:\"answer\";s:239:\"Common warning signs include: AC blowing warm air, weak airflow, strange noises (grinding, squealing, or banging), unusual odors, excessive cycling on/off, high humidity indoors, water leaks around the unit, or unusually high energy bills.\";}i:7;a:2:{s:8:\"question\";s:28:\"Can I prevent AC breakdowns?\";s:6:\"answer\";s:270:\"Regular maintenance is the best prevention. We recommend annual AC tune-ups, changing filters every 1-3 months, keeping outdoor units clear of debris, and addressing small issues before they become major problems. Our maintenance plans help prevent 80% of AC breakdowns.\";}}'),
(449,108,'neighborhoods','Downtown Miami\nBrickell\nCoral Way\nLittle Havana\nCoconut Grove\nWynwood\nDesign District\nEdgewater\nMidtown Miami\nOvertown\nAllapattah\nMiami Shores\nUpper Eastside\nMorningside\nBuena Vista\nLittle Haiti\nFlagami\nWest Flagler\nThe Roads\nCoral Gate\nSilver Bluff'),
(450,108,'climate_note','Miami\'s humid subtropical climate creates year-round demand for air conditioning, with summer temperatures regularly exceeding 90F and humidity levels averaging 75-80%. The constant operation puts significant strain on AC systems, making regular maintenance and prompt repairs essential. Salt air from the nearby ocean can also accelerate corrosion of HVAC components, particularly in coastal neighborhoods like Brickell and Edgewater.'),
(451,108,'service_area_note','<p><strong>Serving Miami Since 2005</strong></p>\n\n<p>Sunnyside AC has been providing expert HVAC services to Miami residents and businesses for nearly two decades. We\'re intimately familiar with the unique challenges of cooling Miami properties, from high-rise condos in Brickell to historic homes in Coral Gables.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Average Response Time:</strong> 45 minutes in greater Miami area</p>\n\n<p><strong>Local Expertise:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>High-rise condo HVAC systems in Downtown and Brickell</li>\n<li>Historic home cooling solutions in Coral Gables and Coconut Grove</li>\n<li>Commercial HVAC for Wynwood and Design District businesses</li>\n<li>Multi-family residential buildings throughout Miami-Dade</li>\n<li>Coastal property HVAC maintenance and corrosion prevention</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Miami Building Codes & Permits:</strong> Our technicians are well-versed in Miami-Dade County building codes and permitting requirements for HVAC installations, replacements, and major repairs. We handle all permit applications and ensure full code compliance.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Hurricane Preparedness:</strong> Living in Miami means preparing for hurricane season. We offer pre-storm AC system inspections and post-storm emergency repairs to get your cooling back online quickly after severe weather.</p>'),
(452,108,'city_video_url','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lqWe6XnSmrQ'),
(453,108,'city_video_title','HVAC Services in Miami, Florida | Expert Air Conditioning Repair'),
(454,108,'city_video_description','Watch our certified HVAC technicians providing expert air conditioning and heating services throughout Miami. See how we serve customers in Brickell, Coral Gables, Wynwood, and all of Miami-Dade County with professional, reliable HVAC solutions.'),
(455,108,'city_video_duration','PT2M45S'),
