(826,60,'_service_process_2_description','field_process_step_description'),
(827,60,'service_process_3_title','Professional Replacement'),
(828,60,'_service_process_3_title','field_process_step_title'),
(829,60,'service_process_3_description','Our certified team removes your old system and installs your new AC following all codes and manufacturer specifications. Most replacements complete in one day.'),
(830,60,'_service_process_3_description','field_process_step_description'),
(831,60,'service_process_4_title','Testing & Training'),
(832,60,'_service_process_4_title','field_process_step_title'),
(833,60,'service_process_4_description','We test all components, calibrate performance, program your thermostat, and train you on operating your new energy-efficient system.'),
(834,60,'_service_process_4_description','field_process_step_description'),
(835,60,'service_process','5'),
(836,60,'_service_process','field_service_process'),
(837,60,'service_faqs_0_question','How do I know if I need AC replacement or just repair?'),
(838,60,'_service_faqs_0_question','field_faq_question'),
(839,60,'service_faqs_0_answer','Consider replacement if your system is over 10-12 years old, requires frequent repairs, has refrigerant leaks (especially R-22), repair costs exceed 50% of replacement, energy bills keep rising, or it can\'t maintain comfort. We provide honest assessments and explain all options so you can make an informed decision.'),
(840,60,'_service_faqs_0_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(841,60,'service_faqs_1_question','How long does AC replacement take?'),
(842,60,'_service_faqs_1_question','field_faq_question'),
(843,60,'service_faqs_1_answer','Most residential AC replacements are completed in 6-10 hours, typically in a single day. Complex installations or larger systems may require 1-2 days. We provide a clear timeline during your consultation and work efficiently to minimize disruption to your home.'),
(844,60,'_service_faqs_1_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(845,60,'service_faqs_2_question','How much does AC replacement cost?'),
(846,60,'_service_faqs_2_question','field_faq_question'),
(847,60,'service_faqs_2_answer','AC replacement typically costs $3,500-$12,000 depending on system size, efficiency rating (SEER), brand, and installation complexity. Higher-efficiency systems cost more upfront but deliver significant energy savings. We provide free assessments with transparent pricing and financing options with approved credit.'),
(848,60,'_service_faqs_2_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(849,60,'service_faqs_3_question','What size AC system do I need?'),
(850,60,'_service_faqs_3_question','field_faq_question'),
(851,60,'service_faqs_3_answer','We perform Manual J load calculations considering your home\'s square footage, insulation, windows, ceiling height, orientation, and local climate. Proper sizing is crucialoversized systems waste energy and don\'t dehumidify properly, while undersized systems run constantly and wear out faster. We handle all sizing professionally.'),
(852,60,'_service_faqs_3_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(853,60,'service_faqs_4_question','Should I upgrade to a high-efficiency AC system?'),
(854,60,'_service_faqs_4_question','field_faq_question'),
(855,60,'service_faqs_4_answer','High-efficiency systems (16-20 SEER) cost 20-40% more upfront but can reduce cooling costs by 30-50%, typically paying for themselves in 5-8 years. They also qualify for rebates and tax credits. We help you calculate the payback period and total cost of ownership to make the best decision.'),
(856,60,'_service_faqs_4_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(857,60,'service_faqs_5_question','What brands do you recommend for AC replacement?'),
(858,60,'_service_faqs_5_question','field_faq_question'),
(859,60,'service_faqs_5_answer','We install premium brands like Carrier, Trane, and Lennox for maximum reliability, plus excellent value brands like Goodman, Rheem, and York. We\'ll recommend specific models based on your budget, efficiency goals, and feature preferences. All brands we install come with strong manufacturer warranties.'),
(860,60,'_service_faqs_5_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(861,60,'service_faqs_6_question','Can I replace just the outdoor unit or indoor unit?'),
(862,60,'_service_faqs_6_question','field_faq_question'),
(863,60,'service_faqs_6_answer','While possible, we typically don\'t recommend it. Mismatched systems reduce efficiency, void warranties, and may violate building codes. Modern AC systems are engineered as matched sets. Replacing both units ensures optimal performance, full warranty coverage, and maximum energy savings.'),
(864,60,'_service_faqs_6_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(865,60,'service_faqs_7_question','Do you offer financing for AC replacement?'),
(866,60,'_service_faqs_7_question','field_faq_question'),
(867,60,'service_faqs_7_answer','Yes, we offer flexible financing options with approved credit, including low monthly payments and promotional financing. We also help you access manufacturer rebates (often $300-$1,200), utility company incentives, and federal tax credits (up to $600 for qualifying high-efficiency systems) to reduce your total investment.'),
(868,60,'_service_faqs_7_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(869,60,'service_faqs_8_question','What warranty comes with AC replacement?'),
(870,60,'_service_faqs_8_question','field_faq_question'),
(871,60,'service_faqs_8_answer','New AC systems include manufacturer warranties on parts (typically 5-10 years, sometimes lifetime on compressor) plus our comprehensive labor warranty. We register your warranty and provide all documentation. Extended warranty options are available for additional coverage and peace of mind.'),
(872,60,'_service_faqs_8_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(873,60,'service_faqs_9_question','Will a new AC system lower my energy bills?'),
(874,60,'_service_faqs_9_question','field_faq_question'),
(875,60,'service_faqs_9_answer','Yes! Modern high-efficiency systems (16+ SEER) can reduce cooling costs by 30-50% compared to older 10-12 SEER units. A typical South Florida home spending $200/month on cooling could save $60-$100/month. We provide energy savings estimates during your consultation so you know exactly what to expect.'),
(876,60,'_service_faqs_9_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(877,60,'service_faqs','10'),
(878,60,'_service_faqs','field_service_faqs'),
(879,61,'service_description','Heat pumps are one of the most versatile and energy-efficient HVAC solutions available, providing both cooling and heating from a single system. At Sunnyside AC, we specialize in heat pump installation, repair, and replacement services throughout South Florida. Our certified technicians have over 20 years of experience working with all major heat pump brands and understand the unique advantages these systems offer in our moderate climate.\n\nUnlike traditional AC systems that only cool, heat pumps transfer heat in both directionsremoving heat from your home in summer for cooling, and extracting heat from outdoor air to warm your home in winter. This makes them exceptionally efficient, using 50-75% less energy than electric resistance heating. While South Florida doesn\'t experience extreme cold, heat pumps excel in our mild winters (rarely below 40F), providing comfortable, cost-effective heating on those occasional chilly nights without requiring a separate furnace.\n\nWe install and service all major heat pump brands including Carrier, Trane, Lennox, Goodman, Rheem, York, American Standard, Bryant, Daikin, and Mitsubishi. Modern heat pumps achieve SEER ratings of 16-22 for cooling and HSPF ratings of 8.5-13 for heating, delivering exceptional year-round energy efficiency. Many South Florida homeowners save 30-40% on their annual HVAC energy costs by switching to a high-efficiency heat pump system.\n\nOur heat pump services include new installations with complete load calculations and sizing, system replacements for aging or inefficient units, repairs for all makes and models, seasonal maintenance and tune-ups, refrigerant leak detection and repair, compressor and reversing valve diagnostics, thermostat upgrades including smart thermostats, and emergency 24/7 service. We handle all permits and ensure every installation meets manufacturer specifications and Florida building codes.\n\nHeat pumps are ideal for South Florida homes because they provide efficient cooling during our long hot season (March-November) and energy-efficient heating during brief cold snaps (December-February). They\'re especially cost-effective if you currently use electric resistance heat or have eliminated gas service. We offer free consultations to determine if a heat pump is right for your home, with flexible financing options and help accessing available rebates and tax credits for qualifying high-efficiency systems.'),
