(918,61,'service_process','5'),
(919,61,'_service_process','field_service_process'),
(920,61,'service_faqs_0_question','What is a heat pump and how does it work?'),
(921,61,'_service_faqs_0_question','field_faq_question'),
(922,61,'service_faqs_0_answer','A heat pump is a versatile HVAC system that provides both heating and cooling. It works by transferring heat rather than generating it. In summer, it removes heat from your home like a traditional AC. In winter, it extracts heat from outdoor air (even when it feels cold) and transfers it inside. This makes it 2-3 times more efficient than electric resistance heating.'),
(923,61,'_service_faqs_0_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(924,61,'service_faqs_1_question','Do heat pumps work well in South Florida?'),
(925,61,'_service_faqs_1_question','field_faq_question'),
(926,61,'service_faqs_1_answer','Yes, heat pumps are ideal for South Florida! They excel in mild climates and work efficiently down to 25-40F depending on the model. Since our winters rarely drop below 40F, heat pumps provide cost-effective heating on cool nights while delivering excellent cooling performance during our long hot season.'),
(927,61,'_service_faqs_1_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(928,61,'service_faqs_2_question','How much can I save with a heat pump?'),
(929,61,'_service_faqs_2_question','field_faq_question'),
(930,61,'service_faqs_2_answer','Heat pumps can reduce your heating energy costs by 50-75% compared to electric resistance heat (baseboard heaters, space heaters, or heat strips). For cooling, modern high-efficiency heat pumps (16+ SEER) save 30-40% compared to older AC systems. Total annual savings typically range from $400-$1,200 depending on your current system and usage.'),
(931,61,'_service_faqs_2_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(932,61,'service_faqs_3_question','What\'s the difference between a heat pump and regular AC?'),
(933,61,'_service_faqs_3_question','field_faq_question'),
(934,61,'service_faqs_3_answer','A heat pump looks similar to an AC but includes a reversing valve that allows it to provide both heating and cooling. Traditional AC systems only cool. If you currently have separate AC and electric heat, a heat pump combines both functions in one efficient system, saving space and reducing energy costs.'),
(935,61,'_service_faqs_3_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(936,61,'service_faqs_4_question','How much does a heat pump installation cost?'),
(937,61,'_service_faqs_4_question','field_faq_question'),
(938,61,'service_faqs_4_answer','Heat pump installation typically costs $4,000-$10,000 depending on system size, efficiency rating (SEER/HSPF), brand, and installation complexity. While slightly more expensive than AC-only systems, the heating capability and energy savings typically provide payback within 3-6 years. Financing and rebates are available.'),
(939,61,'_service_faqs_4_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(940,61,'service_faqs_5_question','What brands of heat pumps do you install?'),
(941,61,'_service_faqs_5_question','field_faq_question'),
(942,61,'service_faqs_5_answer','We install all major heat pump brands including Carrier, Trane, Lennox (premium reliability), Goodman, Rheem, York (excellent value), American Standard, Bryant, Daikin, and Mitsubishi (ductless mini-split heat pumps). We\'ll recommend the best brand and model for your specific needs and budget.'),
(943,61,'_service_faqs_5_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(944,61,'service_faqs_6_question','Do heat pumps require special maintenance?'),
(945,61,'_service_faqs_6_question','field_faq_question'),
(946,61,'service_faqs_6_answer','Heat pumps need the same basic maintenance as regular AC systemsannual tune-ups, filter changes every 1-3 months, and keeping outdoor units clear. We also check the reversing valve, defrost controls, and test both heating and cooling modes to ensure year-round reliability.'),
(947,61,'_service_faqs_6_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(948,61,'service_faqs_7_question','Can you add a heat pump to existing ductwork?'),
(949,61,'_service_faqs_7_question','field_faq_question'),
(950,61,'service_faqs_7_answer','Yes! If you have existing ductwork in good condition, we can typically install a ducted heat pump using your current ducts. We\'ll inspect and seal any leaks for optimal efficiency. For homes without ducts, we offer ductless mini-split heat pumps that don\'t require ductwork.'),
(951,61,'_service_faqs_7_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(952,61,'service_faqs_8_question','Are heat pumps eligible for rebates or tax credits?'),
(953,61,'_service_faqs_8_question','field_faq_question'),
(954,61,'service_faqs_8_answer','Yes! High-efficiency heat pumps (meeting specific SEER/HSPF requirements) often qualify for manufacturer rebates ($300-$1,500), utility company incentives, and federal tax credits (up to $2,000 for qualifying systems under recent legislation). We help you identify and apply for all available incentives.'),
(955,61,'_service_faqs_8_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(956,61,'service_faqs_9_question','What size heat pump do I need for my home?'),
(957,61,'_service_faqs_9_question','field_faq_question'),
(958,61,'service_faqs_9_answer','We determine the correct size through Manual J load calculations, considering your home\'s square footage, insulation, windows, orientation, and local climate. Proper sizing is criticaloversized heat pumps short-cycle and waste energy, while undersized units can\'t maintain comfort. We handle all sizing professionally to ensure optimal performance.'),
(959,61,'_service_faqs_9_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(960,61,'service_faqs','10'),
(961,61,'_service_faqs','field_service_faqs'),
(962,166,'rank_math_internal_links_processed','1'),
(963,166,'_wp_page_template','default'),
(964,63,'service_description','While South Florida is known for its heat, those occasional cold snaps during winter months can make a broken heating system uncomfortable and even unsafe for families. At Sunnyside AC, we provide fast, reliable heating repair services throughout South Florida for all types of heating systems including heat pumps, furnaces, electric heat strips, and ductless mini-splits. Our certified HVAC technicians have over 20 years of experience diagnosing and repairing heating problems quickly and effectively.\n\nCommon heating problems we repair include the heater not turning on, blowing cold air instead of warm air, insufficient heat or weak airflow, strange noises (banging, rattling, squealing), thermostat malfunctions, pilot light or ignition problems, frequent cycling on and off, unusual odors from vents, high energy bills with poor heating performance, and emergency heat running constantly. We understand that heating issues often occur during the coldest nights when you need warmth most, which is why we offer same-day service and emergency heating repairs throughout South Florida.\n\nWe service all major heating system brands including Carrier, Trane, Lennox, Goodman, Rheem, York, American Standard, Bryant, Daikin, Mitsubishi, and more. Whether you have a heat pump, gas furnace, electric furnace, or ductless mini-split heating system, our technicians arrive fully equipped with diagnostic tools and common replacement parts to complete most heating repairs in a single visit. We specialize in heat pump reversing valve repairs, compressor diagnostics, defrost control issues, thermostat problems, and emergency heat strip failures.\n\nEvery heating repair begins with a comprehensive diagnostic inspection using advanced testing equipment. We identify the root cause of your heating problemnot just the symptomsand provide upfront, transparent pricing before starting any work. Our technicians explain what\'s wrong, what repair options you have, and what we recommend based on your system\'s age, condition, and repair cost versus replacement value. We believe in honest assessments and never pressure you into unnecessary repairs.\n\nAll heating repairs are backed by our workmanship warranty and come with a satisfaction guarantee. We use high-quality OEM and approved replacement parts to ensure reliable, long-lasting repairs. Our goal is to restore your home\'s warmth quickly and keep your heating system running efficiently throughout South Florida\'s brief but sometimes surprisingly chilly winter season. We also provide preventive maintenance recommendations to help you avoid future heating breakdowns.'),
