(1002,63,'_service_process_4_description','field_process_step_description'),
(1003,63,'service_process','5'),
(1004,63,'_service_process','field_service_process'),
(1005,63,'service_faqs_0_question','Do you offer emergency heating repair service?'),
(1006,63,'_service_faqs_0_question','field_faq_question'),
(1007,63,'service_faqs_0_answer','Yes, we provide 24/7 emergency heating repair service throughout South Florida. We understand that heating problems often occur during the coldest nights when you need warmth most. Call us anytime and we\'ll prioritize your heating emergency, often arriving within 2-4 hours.'),
(1008,63,'_service_faqs_0_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1009,63,'service_faqs_1_question','Why is my heater blowing cold air?'),
(1010,63,'_service_faqs_1_question','field_faq_question'),
(1011,63,'service_faqs_1_answer','Common causes include thermostat set incorrectly (on \"cool\" or \"fan only\"), heat pump reversing valve stuck in cooling mode, defrost cycle running (heat pumps), pilot light or ignition failure (furnaces), low refrigerant in heat pumps, or emergency heat strips failed. We diagnose the exact cause and provide cost-effective repair solutions.'),
(1012,63,'_service_faqs_1_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1013,63,'service_faqs_2_question','How much does heating repair cost?'),
(1014,63,'_service_faqs_2_question','field_faq_question'),
(1015,63,'service_faqs_2_answer','Heating repair costs vary by problem. Simple fixes like thermostat replacement ($150-$300) or ignitor replacement ($200-$400) are affordable. Major repairs like reversing valve replacement ($800-$1,500) or heat exchanger replacement ($1,000-$2,000) cost more. We always provide upfront pricing before starting work.'),
(1016,63,'_service_faqs_2_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1017,63,'service_faqs_3_question','What heating systems do you repair?'),
(1018,63,'_service_faqs_3_question','field_faq_question'),
(1019,63,'service_faqs_3_answer','We repair all types of heating systems including heat pumps (most common in South Florida), electric furnaces, gas furnaces, ductless mini-split heating systems, and electric heat strips (emergency heat). Our technicians are trained on all major brands and heating technologies.'),
(1020,63,'_service_faqs_3_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1021,63,'service_faqs_4_question','Should I repair or replace my heating system?'),
(1022,63,'_service_faqs_4_question','field_faq_question'),
(1023,63,'service_faqs_4_answer','Consider replacement if your system is over 12-15 years old, requires frequent repairs, repair costs exceed 50% of replacement cost, or can\'t maintain comfortable temperatures. For newer systems or minor issues, repair is usually more cost-effective. We provide honest recommendations based on your specific situation.'),
(1024,63,'_service_faqs_4_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1025,63,'service_faqs_5_question','Why isn\'t my heat pump switching to heating mode?'),
(1026,63,'_service_faqs_5_question','field_faq_question'),
(1027,63,'service_faqs_5_answer','This is typically caused by a faulty reversing valve (the component that switches between heating and cooling), defrost control issues, thermostat wiring problems, or low refrigerant levels. Our technicians can diagnose and repair reversing valve problems, which are common in heat pumps but often fixable without full system replacement.'),
(1028,63,'_service_faqs_5_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1029,63,'service_faqs_6_question','How quickly can you repair my heating system?'),
(1030,63,'_service_faqs_6_question','field_faq_question'),
(1031,63,'service_faqs_6_answer','We offer same-day service and can often arrive within 2-4 hours for heating emergencies. Most heating repairs take 1-3 hours to complete. Our service vehicles carry common replacement parts, allowing us to complete most repairs during the first visit without ordering parts.'),
(1032,63,'_service_faqs_6_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1033,63,'service_faqs_7_question','Is heating maintenance important in South Florida?'),
(1034,63,'_service_faqs_7_question','field_faq_question'),
(1035,63,'service_faqs_7_answer','Yes! While we don\'t use heat often, neglected heating systems fail when you need them mostduring those occasional cold snaps. Annual maintenance (ideally before winter) ensures your heat pump or furnace is ready when temperatures drop. Preventive maintenance prevents 80% of heating breakdowns.'),
(1036,63,'_service_faqs_7_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1037,63,'service_faqs_8_question','What brands of heating systems do you service?'),
(1038,63,'_service_faqs_8_question','field_faq_question'),
(1039,63,'service_faqs_8_answer','We repair all major heating system brands including Carrier, Trane, Lennox, Goodman, Rheem, York, American Standard, Bryant, Daikin, Mitsubishi, Amana, Ruud, and more. Our technicians receive ongoing training on all major manufacturers and heating technologies.'),
(1040,63,'_service_faqs_8_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1041,63,'service_faqs_9_question','Do you warranty your heating repairs?'),
(1042,63,'_service_faqs_9_question','field_faq_question'),
(1043,63,'service_faqs_9_answer','Yes, all heating repairs include our comprehensive workmanship warranty. Parts warranties vary by manufacturer, typically ranging from 1-5 years. We stand behind our work 100% and provide ongoing support to ensure your heating system operates reliably.'),
(1044,63,'_service_faqs_9_answer','field_faq_answer'),
