(1171,65,'_service_process','field_service_process'),
(1172,65,'service_faqs_0_question','When should I replace my heating system?'),
(1173,65,'_service_faqs_0_question','field_faq_question'),
(1174,65,'service_faqs_0_answer','Consider replacement if your system is 12-15+ years old, requires frequent repairs, repair costs exceed 50% of replacement, can\'t maintain comfortable heat, or uses R-22 refrigerant (heat pumps). We provide honest assessments to help you make the best decision.'),
(1175,65,'_service_faqs_0_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1176,65,'service_faqs_1_question','How much does heating replacement cost?'),
(1177,65,'_service_faqs_1_question','field_faq_question'),
(1178,65,'service_faqs_1_answer','Heating replacement costs: heat pumps $4,000-$10,000 (includes cooling), electric furnaces $2,500-$5,500, gas furnaces $3,000-$7,000, ductless mini-splits $3,500-$9,000. Higher efficiency saves money long-term. We offer financing and help with rebates.'),
(1179,65,'_service_faqs_1_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1180,65,'service_faqs_2_question','What type of heating system should I install in South Florida?'),
(1181,65,'_service_faqs_2_question','field_faq_question'),
(1182,65,'service_faqs_2_answer','Heat pumps are ideal for South Florida because they provide exceptional cooling (our main need) plus efficient heating for mild wintersall from one system. They\'re 2-3X more efficient than electric resistance heat and perfect for our climate.'),
(1183,65,'_service_faqs_2_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1184,65,'service_faqs_3_question','How long does heating replacement take?'),
(1185,65,'_service_faqs_3_question','field_faq_question'),
(1186,65,'service_faqs_3_answer','Most heating replacements are completed in 6-10 hours, typically in one day. Heat pump systems may take slightly longer since they provide both heating and cooling. We provide clear timelines and work efficiently.'),
(1187,65,'_service_faqs_3_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1188,65,'service_faqs_4_question','Will a new heating system lower my energy bills?'),
(1189,65,'_service_faqs_4_question','field_faq_question'),
(1190,65,'service_faqs_4_answer','Yes! Modern high-efficiency heating systems can reduce heating costs by 50-75% compared to older units. Heat pumps also dramatically reduce cooling costs (30-50% savings), providing year-round savings for South Florida homeowners.'),
(1191,65,'_service_faqs_4_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1192,65,'service_faqs_5_question','What brands do you recommend?'),
(1193,65,'_service_faqs_5_question','field_faq_question'),
(1194,65,'service_faqs_5_answer','We recommend premium brands like Carrier, Trane, and Lennox for maximum reliability, or value brands like Goodman, Rheem, and York. All brands we install come with strong warranties and proven performance in Florida\'s climate.'),
(1195,65,'_service_faqs_5_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1196,65,'service_faqs_6_question','Do you offer financing for heating replacement?'),
(1197,65,'_service_faqs_6_question','field_faq_question'),
(1198,65,'service_faqs_6_answer','Yes, we offer flexible financing with approved credit. We also help you access manufacturer rebates, utility incentives, and federal tax credits (up to $2,000 for qualifying high-efficiency systems) to reduce your investment.'),
(1199,65,'_service_faqs_6_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1200,65,'service_faqs_7_question','Can I replace just the heating component?'),
(1201,65,'_service_faqs_7_question','field_faq_question'),
(1202,65,'service_faqs_7_answer','For heat pumps (which heat AND cool), we typically recommend replacing both indoor and outdoor units as a matched system for optimal efficiency and warranty coverage. For furnaces or supplemental heat, standalone replacement is common.'),
(1203,65,'_service_faqs_7_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1204,65,'service_faqs','8'),
(1205,65,'_service_faqs','field_service_faqs'),
(1206,66,'service_description','While furnaces aren\'t as common in South Florida as they are in northern climates, many homes still rely on electric or gas furnaces for heating during cooler months. At Sunnyside AC, we provide complete furnace services including installation, replacement, repair, and maintenance for both electric and gas furnaces throughout South Florida. Our certified HVAC technicians have extensive experience with all major furnace brands and models.\n\nFurnaces work by heating air and distributing it through your home\'s ductwork. Electric furnaces use heating elements (similar to large toasters) to warm air, while gas furnaces burn natural gas to create heat. For South Florida\'s mild climate, furnaces provide reliable supplemental heat during occasional cold snaps without the expense of systems designed for harsh northern winters. Electric furnaces are particularly popular here since they\'re cost-effective for limited seasonal use.\n\nWe service and install all major furnace brands including Carrier, Trane, Lennox, Goodman, Rheem, York, American Standard, Bryant, and more. Our furnace services include new furnace installations for homes without heating, furnace replacements for aging or failed systems, furnace repairs for all makes and models, seasonal maintenance and tune-ups, thermostat installation and upgrades, ductwork inspection and sealing, safety inspections and carbon monoxide testing (gas furnaces), and emergency 24/7 furnace repair service.\n\nCommon furnace problems we address include the furnace not turning on, blowing cold air, insufficient heat output, pilot light or ignition problems (gas furnaces), strange noises (banging, rattling), frequent cycling, thermostat malfunctions, high energy bills, and unusual odors. We diagnose the exact problem and provide upfront pricing before starting any repair work.\n\nFor South Florida homes, we help you determine if a furnace is the best heating solution or if alternatives like heat pumps (which provide both heating and cooling) might offer better value. We provide free consultations, explain all options, and help you make the most cost-effective decision for your home\'s comfort needs and budget.'),
