(1246,66,'_service_process','field_service_process'),
(1247,66,'service_faqs_0_question','Are furnaces common in South Florida?'),
(1248,66,'_service_faqs_0_question','field_faq_question'),
(1249,66,'service_faqs_0_answer','Furnaces are less common than heat pumps in South Florida but still found in many homes. Electric furnaces are more popular here than gas furnaces since they\'re cost-effective for our limited heating needs. Many homeowners are switching to heat pumps that provide both heating and cooling.'),
(1250,66,'_service_faqs_0_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1251,66,'service_faqs_1_question','Electric vs gas furnace - which is better for Florida?'),
(1252,66,'_service_faqs_1_question','field_faq_question'),
(1253,66,'service_faqs_1_answer','Electric furnaces are generally better for South Florida since we use heat infrequently. They cost less to install, require less maintenance, and don\'t need gas lines. Gas furnaces are more efficient for heavy use but less necessary in our mild climate.'),
(1254,66,'_service_faqs_1_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1255,66,'service_faqs_2_question','How much does furnace installation cost?'),
(1256,66,'_service_faqs_2_question','field_faq_question'),
(1257,66,'service_faqs_2_answer','Electric furnace installation typically costs $2,500-$5,000. Gas furnace installation costs $3,000-$7,000 (more if gas lines need to be installed). We provide free consultations with detailed pricing and can also quote heat pump alternatives.'),
(1258,66,'_service_faqs_2_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1259,66,'service_faqs_3_question','Should I replace my furnace with a heat pump?'),
(1260,66,'_service_faqs_3_question','field_faq_question'),
(1261,66,'service_faqs_3_answer','Many South Florida homeowners choose this upgrade. Heat pumps provide both efficient cooling (your main need) and cost-effective heating from one system. They\'re 2-3X more efficient than furnaces for heating and excellent for cooling. We\'ll help you compare options.'),
(1262,66,'_service_faqs_3_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1263,66,'service_faqs_4_question','How long do furnaces last in South Florida?'),
(1264,66,'_service_faqs_4_question','field_faq_question'),
(1265,66,'service_faqs_4_answer','Furnaces typically last 15-20 years in South Florida, often longer than northern climates since we use them infrequently. With annual maintenance, many furnaces provide reliable service for two decades. Age 15+ is when replacement should be considered.'),
(1266,66,'_service_faqs_4_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1267,66,'service_faqs_5_question','Do gas furnaces work during power outages?'),
(1268,66,'_service_faqs_5_question','field_faq_question'),
(1269,66,'service_faqs_5_answer','No, even gas furnaces require electricity to power the blower fan, thermostat, and ignition system. If you need backup heat during outages, consider a whole-home generator. Heat pumps and electric furnaces also require power.'),
(1270,66,'_service_faqs_5_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1271,66,'service_faqs','6'),
(1272,66,'_service_faqs','field_service_faqs'),
(1273,67,'service_description','Indoor air quality is crucial for your family\'s health and comfort, especially in South Florida where homes are sealed tight against heat and humidity. At Sunnyside AC, we specialize in indoor air quality solutions that remove pollutants, control humidity, eliminate odors, and create healthier indoor environments. Our certified technicians install and service air purifiers, UV lights, whole-home humidifiers and dehumidifiers, ventilation systems, and advanced filtration systems.\n\nPoor indoor air quality causes allergies, asthma symptoms, respiratory problems, headaches, fatigue, and long-term health issues. Common indoor air pollutants in South Florida homes include mold spores (thrives in humidity), dust mites, pollen, pet dander, volatile organic compounds (VOCs) from cleaning products and furniture, bacteria and viruses, and odors from cooking, pets, or smoking. Our air quality solutions address all these issues systematically.\n\nWe install and service premium air quality products including UV germicidal lights (kills mold, bacteria, and viruses in your HVAC system), whole-home air purifiers (HEPA and electronic filters remove 99.97% of particles), dehumidifiers (critical for South Florida\'s humidity), energy recovery ventilators (fresh air without energy waste), advanced media filters (capture microscopic particles), and duct cleaning and sealing services. All systems integrate seamlessly with your existing HVAC equipment.\n\nIndoor air quality is especially important for families with children, elderly members, asthma or allergy sufferers, pets, smokers, or anyone who spends significant time indoors (which is most of us in South Florida\'s hot climate). We provide free indoor air quality assessments, explain which solutions address your specific concerns, and install systems that work quietly and efficiently in the background.\n\nOur indoor air quality solutions typically pay for themselves through reduced medical expenses, fewer sick days, better sleep quality, and lower HVAC maintenance costs (cleaner air means cleaner equipment). We offer flexible financing and help you prioritize which improvements deliver the most benefit for your budget and family\'s health.'),
