(1313,67,'_service_process','field_service_process'),
(1314,67,'service_faqs_0_question','What are signs of poor indoor air quality?'),
(1315,67,'_service_faqs_0_question','field_faq_question'),
(1316,67,'service_faqs_0_answer','Common signs include frequent allergies or asthma symptoms, excessive dust, musty odors, visible mold, condensation on windows, stuffiness, unexplained headaches or fatigue, and respiratory issues that improve when you leave home. South Florida\'s humidity makes air quality issues especially common.'),
(1317,67,'_service_faqs_0_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1318,67,'service_faqs_1_question','How much do air quality systems cost?'),
(1319,67,'_service_faqs_1_question','field_faq_question'),
(1320,67,'service_faqs_1_answer','Costs vary by solution: UV lights $500-$1,200, whole-home air purifiers $1,000-$3,000, dehumidifiers $1,500-$3,500, advanced filters $300-$800, energy recovery ventilators $2,000-$4,000. We help you prioritize based on budget and biggest health concerns.'),
(1321,67,'_service_faqs_1_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1322,67,'service_faqs_2_question','Do UV lights really kill mold and bacteria?'),
(1323,67,'_service_faqs_2_question','field_faq_question'),
(1324,67,'service_faqs_2_answer','Yes! UV-C germicidal lights installed in your HVAC system kill up to 99.9% of mold, bacteria, and viruses that pass through. They\'re especially valuable in humid South Florida where mold thrives. UV lights also keep your AC coils clean, improving efficiency.'),
(1325,67,'_service_faqs_2_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1326,67,'service_faqs_3_question','Should I get a whole-home dehumidifier in Florida?'),
(1327,67,'_service_faqs_3_question','field_faq_question'),
(1328,67,'service_faqs_3_answer','Absolutely! South Florida\'s humidity (often 75-85%) promotes mold growth, dust mites, and discomfort. Whole-home dehumidifiers maintain ideal 40-50% indoor humidity, preventing mold, reducing allergens, and making your AC more efficient. They\'re one of the best investments for Florida homes.'),
(1329,67,'_service_faqs_3_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1330,67,'service_faqs_4_question','What\'s better - portable or whole-home air purifiers?'),
(1331,67,'_service_faqs_4_question','field_faq_question'),
(1332,67,'service_faqs_4_answer','Whole-home systems are superior for comprehensive coverage. They integrate with your HVAC to clean air throughout your entire home automatically, while portable units only clean one room and require manual operation. Whole-home systems are also quieter and more efficient.'),
(1333,67,'_service_faqs_4_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1334,67,'service_faqs_5_question','How often should I change air filters?'),
(1335,67,'_service_faqs_5_question','field_faq_question'),
(1336,67,'service_faqs_5_answer','Standard 1-inch filters: every 1-3 months. Thicker media filters: every 6-12 months. HEPA filters: annually. In South Florida\'s dusty, humid environment, we recommend checking filters monthly and changing when dirty. Clean filters improve air quality and HVAC efficiency significantly.'),
(1337,67,'_service_faqs_5_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1338,67,'service_faqs','6'),
(1339,67,'_service_faqs','field_service_faqs'),
(1340,68,'service_description','Ductless mini-split systems are one of the most versatile and energy-efficient HVAC solutions available, perfect for South Florida homes without existing ductwork, room additions, converted garages, or homes where traditional ducted systems aren\'t practical. At Sunnyside AC, we specialize in ductless mini-split installation, repair, and maintenance throughout South Florida. Our certified technicians have extensive experience with premium ductless brands including Mitsubishi, Daikin, Fujitsu, LG, and Carrier.\n\nDuctless mini-splits consist of an outdoor compressor unit connected to one or more indoor air handlers via small refrigerant lines that run through a 3-inch hole in the wall. This eliminates the need for bulky ductwork while providing precise temperature control for individual rooms or zones. Each indoor unit operates independently with its own remote control or smart thermostat, allowing different family members to set their preferred temperatures in different roomsperfect for South Florida homes where cooling needs vary by room orientation and sun exposure.\n\nModern ductless mini-split systems achieve exceptional efficiency ratings of 18-30+ SEER for cooling and 9-12+ HSPF for heating, far exceeding traditional central AC systems. This translates to 30-50% lower energy bills compared to window units or older central systems. Since they don\'t lose energy through ductwork (30% energy loss is common in leaky ducts), every dollar you spend on cooling goes directly to comfort. Many South Florida homeowners see complete payback within 3-5 years through energy savings alone.\n\nDuctless mini-splits are ideal for home additions and remodels (no need to extend ductwork), converted garages or Florida rooms, older homes without existing ducts, supplemental cooling for hot rooms, rental properties or ADUs, and homes where duct installation is impractical. They\'re also perfect for South Florida\'s architecturemany homes have concrete block construction, flat or low-slope roofs, and limited attic space where traditional ductwork is difficult or impossible to install.\n\nWe provide complete ductless mini-split services including free home consultations and system design, new installations (single-zone and multi-zone), system replacements and upgrades, repairs for all brands, seasonal maintenance, smart thermostat integration, and 24/7 emergency service. Every installation includes manufacturer warranties (typically 7-12 years), our workmanship warranty, and ongoing support. We help you access available rebates and financing to make ductless mini-splits affordable for any budget.'),
