(1380,68,'_service_process','field_service_process'),
(1381,68,'service_faqs_0_question','What is a ductless mini-split system?'),
(1382,68,'_service_faqs_0_question','field_faq_question'),
(1383,68,'service_faqs_0_answer','A ductless mini-split is an HVAC system with an outdoor compressor unit connected to one or more indoor air handlers without ductwork. Small refrigerant lines run through a 3-inch hole in the wall. Each indoor unit cools (and heats) independently, giving you precise room-by-room temperature control. They\'re ideal for homes without ducts or room additions.'),
(1384,68,'_service_faqs_0_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1385,68,'service_faqs_1_question','How much do ductless mini-splits cost?'),
(1386,68,'_service_faqs_1_question','field_faq_question'),
(1387,68,'service_faqs_1_answer','Single-zone systems: $3,000-$5,500. Multi-zone systems (2-5 rooms): $5,000-$15,000 depending on number of zones, brand, and efficiency. Premium brands like Mitsubishi and Daikin cost more but deliver superior performance and reliability. We offer financing and help you access rebates (often $300-$1,000+ per system).'),
(1388,68,'_service_faqs_1_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1389,68,'service_faqs_2_question','Are ductless mini-splits more efficient than central AC?'),
(1390,68,'_service_faqs_2_question','field_faq_question'),
(1391,68,'service_faqs_2_answer','Yes! Ductless mini-splits achieve 18-30+ SEER efficiency versus 14-18 SEER for most central AC systems. They avoid the 20-30% energy loss from leaky ductwork. Zoning capability means you only cool rooms you\'re using. Most homeowners save 30-50% on cooling costs compared to traditional AC or window units.'),
(1392,68,'_service_faqs_2_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1393,68,'service_faqs_3_question','Can ductless mini-splits heat and cool?'),
(1394,68,'_service_faqs_3_question','field_faq_question'),
(1395,68,'service_faqs_3_answer','Yes! Most ductless mini-splits are heat pumps that provide both cooling and heating. They\'re extremely efficient for heating in South Florida\'s mild winters (more efficient than electric heat). This makes them perfect year-round comfort solutions requiring just one system instead of separate AC and heat.'),
(1396,68,'_service_faqs_3_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1397,68,'service_faqs_4_question','How many rooms can one outdoor unit handle?'),
(1398,68,'_service_faqs_4_question','field_faq_question'),
(1399,68,'service_faqs_4_answer','Multi-zone outdoor units can connect to 2-8 indoor units (zones) depending on the model. Each zone operates independently with its own temperature control. This is perfect for cooling multiple bedrooms, a home addition, or specific rooms without cooling your entire house.'),
(1400,68,'_service_faqs_4_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1401,68,'service_faqs_5_question','Are ductless systems noisy?'),
(1402,68,'_service_faqs_5_question','field_faq_question'),
(1403,68,'service_faqs_5_answer','Indoor units are extremely quiettypically 19-26 decibels (quieter than a whisper). Outdoor units are also quieter than traditional AC condensers. You\'ll barely notice them running, making ductless mini-splits ideal for bedrooms, home offices, and media rooms.'),
(1404,68,'_service_faqs_5_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1405,68,'service_faqs_6_question','What brands of ductless mini-splits do you install?'),
(1406,68,'_service_faqs_6_question','field_faq_question'),
(1407,68,'service_faqs_6_answer','We install premium brands known for reliability and performance: Mitsubishi (industry leader), Daikin (excellent efficiency), Fujitsu (advanced features), LG (great value), and Carrier (trusted name). We help you select the best brand for your needs and budget.'),
(1408,68,'_service_faqs_6_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1409,68,'service_faqs_7_question','Do ductless systems work in South Florida humidity?'),
(1410,68,'_service_faqs_7_question','field_faq_question'),
(1411,68,'service_faqs_7_answer','Absolutely! Modern ductless mini-splits excel at dehumidification, often outperforming traditional AC in humidity control. Many models include dedicated dry mode and intelligent humidity sensors. They\'re perfect for South Florida\'s humid climate and prevent that clammy feeling some AC systems leave behind.'),
(1412,68,'_service_faqs_7_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1413,68,'service_faqs_8_question','How long does ductless installation take?'),
(1414,68,'_service_faqs_8_question','field_faq_question'),
(1415,68,'service_faqs_8_answer','Single-zone installations typically take 4-8 hours and are completed in one day. Multi-zone systems (2-5 zones) take 6-12 hours, often completed in one day but sometimes two days depending on complexity. Installation is much faster than adding ductwork for traditional central AC.'),
(1416,68,'_service_faqs_8_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1417,68,'service_faqs_9_question','What maintenance do ductless mini-splits need?'),
(1418,68,'_service_faqs_9_question','field_faq_question'),
(1419,68,'service_faqs_9_answer','Ductless systems require minimal maintenance: clean indoor unit filters monthly (they slide out easily), annual professional tune-up (clean coils, check refrigerant, test all zones), and keep outdoor unit clear of debris. With proper maintenance, ductless systems last 15-20+ years in South Florida.'),
(1420,68,'_service_faqs_9_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1421,68,'service_faqs','10'),
(1422,68,'_service_faqs','field_service_faqs'),
(1423,69,'service_description','UV germicidal lights are one of the most effective and affordable ways to improve your home\'s indoor air quality while keeping your HVAC system clean and efficient. At Sunnyside AC, we install high-quality UV light systems in air conditioning units throughout South Florida. These powerful lights kill up to 99.9% of mold, bacteria, viruses, and other biological contaminants that grow in your HVAC system and circulate through your home\'s air.\n\nUV-C germicidal lights work by emitting ultraviolet radiation at a specific wavelength (254 nanometers) that destroys the DNA of microorganisms, preventing them from reproducing. Installed inside your air handler near the evaporator coil, UV lights continuously sterilize the air and keep coils free from mold and biofilm buildup. This is especially important in South Florida\'s humid climate where mold thrives in the dark, damp environment of your AC system. Without UV protection, mold can colonize your coils within weeks, reducing efficiency and circulating spores throughout your home.\n\nThe benefits of UV lights extend beyond air quality. By keeping your evaporator coils clean, UV lights maintain optimal heat transfer efficiency, reducing energy consumption by 10-30%. Clean coils also mean better airflow, more consistent cooling, and extended equipment life. Many of our customers report fewer allergy symptoms, reduced odors, and lower electricity bills after UV light installation. The system pays for itself through energy savings and reduced maintenance costs.\n\nWe install premium UV light systems from trusted manufacturers including REME Halo, Field Controls, Honeywell, and Carrier. Our installations include coil sterilization lights (mounted near evaporator coil), air sterilization lights (mounted in return air duct), and whole-home air purification systems with UV technology. All installations come with our workmanship warranty, and UV bulbs typically last 1-2 years before requiring replacementa simple, low-cost maintenance item we can handle during annual tune-ups.\n\nUV lights are particularly beneficial for families with allergies or asthma, homes with mold issues, properties in humid climates like South Florida, anyone concerned about airborne viruses and bacteria, and homeowners who want to reduce HVAC maintenance costs. Installation takes just 1-2 hours, requires no ductwork modifications, and begins improving your air quality immediately. We offer free consultations to determine the ideal UV light solution for your HVAC system and home.'),
