(1463,69,'_service_process','field_service_process'),
(1464,69,'service_faqs_0_question','How do UV lights kill mold and bacteria?'),
(1465,69,'_service_faqs_0_question','field_faq_question'),
(1466,69,'service_faqs_0_answer','UV-C germicidal lights emit ultraviolet radiation at 254 nanometers, a wavelength that destroys the DNA of microorganisms like mold, bacteria, and viruses. This prevents them from reproducing and effectively kills them. The UV light operates 24/7 inside your HVAC system, continuously sterilizing air and preventing biological growth on coils.'),
(1467,69,'_service_faqs_0_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1468,69,'service_faqs_1_question','How much do UV lights cost for HVAC?'),
(1469,69,'_service_faqs_1_question','field_faq_question'),
(1470,69,'service_faqs_1_answer','UV light installation typically costs $500-$1,200 depending on the system type and your AC configuration. Replacement UV bulbs cost $50-$150 and last 12-24 months. Considering energy savings (10-30% reduction) and improved air quality, most systems pay for themselves within 2-3 years through lower electricity bills and reduced maintenance.'),
(1471,69,'_service_faqs_1_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1472,69,'service_faqs_2_question','Are UV lights worth it in South Florida?'),
(1473,69,'_service_faqs_2_question','field_faq_question'),
(1474,69,'service_faqs_2_answer','Absolutely! South Florida\'s humidity creates ideal conditions for mold growth in AC systems. UV lights prevent this mold, keeping your coils clean for better efficiency and preventing mold spores from circulating through your home. They\'re one of the best investments for air quality and HVAC efficiency in our humid climate.'),
(1475,69,'_service_faqs_2_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1476,69,'service_faqs_3_question','Will UV lights help with allergies and asthma?'),
(1477,69,'_service_faqs_3_question','field_faq_question'),
(1478,69,'service_faqs_3_answer','Yes! UV lights kill airborne allergens like mold spores, bacteria, and some viruses that trigger allergy and asthma symptoms. Many customers report significant reduction in symptoms after UV light installation. Combined with quality filters, UV lights create much healthier indoor air for allergy and asthma sufferers.'),
(1479,69,'_service_faqs_3_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1480,69,'service_faqs_4_question','How long do UV bulbs last?'),
(1481,69,'_service_faqs_4_question','field_faq_question'),
(1482,69,'service_faqs_4_answer','Quality UV bulbs typically last 12-24 months with continuous operation. While the bulb still produces visible light after this time, the germicidal UV-C output diminishes. We recommend annual bulb replacement during your AC tune-up to maintain maximum effectiveness. Replacement is quick and affordable ($50-$150).'),
(1483,69,'_service_faqs_4_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1484,69,'service_faqs_5_question','Can I see the UV light working?'),
(1485,69,'_service_faqs_5_question','field_faq_question'),
(1486,69,'service_faqs_5_answer','UV-C light at germicidal wavelengths (254nm) is invisible to the human eye. Some UV lights include a blue indicator light so you can verify operation, but the actual sterilizing UV radiation is not visible. You\'ll notice the results through cleaner coils, better air quality, and reduced odors rather than visible light.'),
(1487,69,'_service_faqs_5_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1488,69,'service_faqs_6_question','Do UV lights eliminate odors from my AC?'),
(1489,69,'_service_faqs_6_question','field_faq_question'),
(1490,69,'service_faqs_6_answer','Yes! Musty or mildew odors from AC vents are caused by mold and bacteria growing on coils and in drain pans. UV lights kill these organisms, eliminating the source of odors. Most customers notice fresher-smelling air within days of UV light installation.'),
(1491,69,'_service_faqs_6_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1492,69,'service_faqs_7_question','Are UV lights safe for my family and pets?'),
(1493,69,'_service_faqs_7_question','field_faq_question'),
(1494,69,'service_faqs_7_answer','Yes, UV lights installed inside your HVAC system are completely safe. The UV-C radiation is contained within the sealed air handler where family and pets never have access. The UV light only affects microorganisms passing through your HVAC system and keeps your breathing air clean and healthy.'),
(1495,69,'_service_faqs_7_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1496,69,'service_faqs_8_question','Will UV lights damage my AC system?'),
(1497,69,'_service_faqs_8_question','field_faq_question'),
(1498,69,'service_faqs_8_answer','No, properly installed UV lights are safe for all HVAC components. Modern UV systems are designed specifically for HVAC installation with appropriate positioning to avoid any negative effects on plastic components. They actually protect your system by preventing biological growth that can damage coils and reduce efficiency.'),
(1499,69,'_service_faqs_8_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1500,69,'service_faqs_9_question','How quickly will I notice results from UV lights?'),
(1501,69,'_service_faqs_9_question','field_faq_question'),
(1502,69,'service_faqs_9_answer','You may notice fresher air and reduced odors within days. Energy savings appear on your next utility bill (typically 10-30% reduction in cooling costs). Visible mold on coils disappears within weeks. Allergy symptoms often improve within 1-2 weeks as mold spore counts drop. UV lights provide both immediate and long-term benefits.'),
(1503,69,'_service_faqs_9_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1504,69,'service_faqs','10'),
(1505,69,'_service_faqs','field_service_faqs'),
(1506,70,'service_description','Air filters are the first line of defense for your HVAC system and your family\'s health, yet they\'re often overlooked until problems arise. At Sunnyside AC, we provide expert air filter services throughout South Florida including filter selection, installation, replacement schedules, and upgrades to high-efficiency filtration systems. Our certified technicians help you choose the right filters for your specific needsbalancing air quality, airflow, and HVAC efficiency.\n\nProper air filtration serves two critical purposes: protecting your HVAC equipment from dust and debris that reduces efficiency and causes breakdowns, and improving your indoor air quality by removing allergens, dust, pollen, pet dander, mold spores, and other airborne particles. In South Florida\'s dusty, pollen-heavy environment with high humidity, quality air filters are essential for both system longevity and healthy indoor air.\n\nWe offer and install all types of air filters including standard disposable filters (MERV 1-4 for basic protection), pleated filters (MERV 8-12 for better filtration), high-efficiency filters (MERV 13-16 for superior air quality), HEPA filters (99.97% particle removal), electrostatic filters (washable, reusable), and whole-home media filters (4-5 inch thickness, 6-12 month lifespan). Each filter type offers different benefits, and we help you select the ideal option based on your air quality concerns, budget, and HVAC system specifications.\n\nFilter replacement frequency depends on several factors. In South Florida, we generally recommend monthly inspection and replacement every 1-3 months for standard 1-inch filters, every 3-6 months for pleated filters, and every 6-12 months for thick media filters. Homes with pets, allergies, or high dust need more frequent changes. Dirty filters restrict airflow, forcing your AC to work harder, increasing energy bills by 15-30%, and potentially causing system damage from frozen coils or compressor failure.\n\nBeyond basic filter replacement, we install permanent whole-home filtration upgrades including 4-5 inch media filter cabinets (replace standard 1-inch slot), electronic air cleaners (charge and trap particles), HEPA filtration systems (hospital-grade air cleaning), and combination systems with UV lights and advanced filters. These upgrades provide dramatically better air quality and longer service intervals. We also offer filter subscription serviceswe deliver the correct filters to your door on a regular schedule so you never forget to change them.'),
(1507,70,'service_benefits_0_benefit','Expert Filter Selection for Your Needs'),
