(1545,70,'service_process','5'),
(1546,70,'_service_process','field_service_process'),
(1547,70,'service_faqs_0_question','How often should I change my air filter in South Florida?'),
(1548,70,'_service_faqs_0_question','field_faq_question'),
(1549,70,'service_faqs_0_answer','Standard 1-inch filters: every 1-3 months. Pleated filters: every 3-6 months. Thick media filters (4-5 inch): every 6-12 months. South Florida\'s dust, pollen, and humidity mean more frequent changes than national averages. Homes with pets or allergies should change monthly. Check monthly and replace when visibly dirty.'),
(1550,70,'_service_faqs_0_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1551,70,'service_faqs_1_question','What MERV rating should I use?'),
(1552,70,'_service_faqs_1_question','field_faq_question'),
(1553,70,'service_faqs_1_answer','MERV 8-11 is ideal for most South Florida homesexcellent filtration without restricting airflow. MERV 13-16 for allergy/asthma sufferers (may require HVAC modifications). MERV 1-4 provides minimal protection. Higher isn\'t always bettertoo high restricts airflow and damages systems. We help you select the right rating for your HVAC system.'),
(1554,70,'_service_faqs_1_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1555,70,'service_faqs_2_question','What happens if I don\'t change my air filter?'),
(1556,70,'_service_faqs_2_question','field_faq_question'),
(1557,70,'service_faqs_2_answer','Dirty filters restrict airflow, causing higher energy bills (15-30% increase), frozen evaporator coils, compressor failure, poor air quality, mold growth in ducts, system overheating, and shortened equipment life. A $20 filter change prevents thousands in repair costs. In South Florida\'s demanding climate, filter maintenance is critical.'),
(1558,70,'_service_faqs_2_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1559,70,'service_faqs_3_question','Are expensive filters worth it?'),
(1560,70,'_service_faqs_3_question','field_faq_question'),
(1561,70,'service_faqs_3_answer','Higher-quality pleated filters (MERV 8-11) are absolutely worth itthey last longer, filter better, and protect your system. However, extremely expensive HEPA filters may restrict airflow unless your system is designed for them. We recommend quality pleated filters for most homes, with whole-home upgrades for serious air quality concerns.'),
(1562,70,'_service_faqs_3_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1563,70,'service_faqs_4_question','Can I upgrade to better filtration?'),
(1564,70,'_service_faqs_4_question','field_faq_question'),
(1565,70,'service_faqs_4_answer','Yes! We install whole-home filtration upgrades including 4-5 inch media filter cabinets (replace thin 1-inch slot), electronic air cleaners, and HEPA systems. These provide dramatically better air quality, longer service intervals (6-12 months), and superior HVAC protection. Upgrades cost $400-$2,000 depending on type.'),
(1566,70,'_service_faqs_4_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1567,70,'service_faqs_5_question','Where is my air filter located?'),
(1568,70,'_service_faqs_5_question','field_faq_question'),
(1569,70,'service_faqs_5_answer','Most filters are in the return air grille (large vent on wall or ceiling), inside the air handler (HVAC closet or attic), or in a filter cabinet near your indoor AC unit. If you can\'t find it, check your HVAC manual or call uswe\'ll locate it and show you how to change it properly.'),
(1570,70,'_service_faqs_5_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1571,70,'service_faqs_6_question','Do all HVAC systems use the same size filter?'),
(1572,70,'_service_faqs_6_question','field_faq_question'),
(1573,70,'service_faqs_6_answer','No, filter sizes vary widely. Common sizes include 16x20x1, 16x25x1, 20x20x1, 20x25x1, but many homes use custom sizes. Check the side of your current filter for the size (like 16x25x1) and always buy exact replacements. Installing wrong-size filters allows unfiltered air to bypass, defeating the purpose.'),
(1574,70,'_service_faqs_6_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1575,70,'service_faqs_7_question','Are washable filters better than disposable?'),
(1576,70,'_service_faqs_7_question','field_faq_question'),
(1577,70,'service_faqs_7_answer','Washable electrostatic filters are reusable and environmentally friendly, but most don\'t filter as well as quality disposable pleated filters. They also require regular washing (every 1-2 months) and must dry completely before reinstalling. For most South Florida homes, quality disposable pleated filters offer better air quality and convenience.'),
(1578,70,'_service_faqs_7_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1579,70,'service_faqs_8_question','Do you offer a filter delivery service?'),
(1580,70,'_service_faqs_8_question','field_faq_question'),
(1581,70,'service_faqs_8_answer','Yes! We offer a filter subscription service where we deliver the correct filters to your door on your replacement schedule (monthly, quarterly, etc.). We\'ll measure your filter size, recommend the ideal type, and send reminders so you never forget to change filters. This simple service prevents costly HVAC problems.'),
(1582,70,'_service_faqs_8_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1583,70,'service_faqs_9_question','Will better filters reduce my allergies?'),
(1584,70,'_service_faqs_9_question','field_faq_question'),
(1585,70,'service_faqs_9_answer','Yes! Quality pleated filters (MERV 8-12) remove most pollen, dust, and pet dander. MERV 13-16 filters remove even smaller particles including mold spores and some bacteria. Combined with UV lights and proper humidity control, advanced filtration significantly reduces allergens. Many customers report dramatic allergy relief after filtration upgrades.'),
(1586,70,'_service_faqs_9_answer','field_faq_answer'),
(1587,70,'service_faqs','10'),
(1588,70,'_service_faqs','field_service_faqs'),
(1589,109,'climate_note','Fort Lauderdale\'s coastal location brings warm subtropical weather year-round, with summer temperatures regularly reaching 89-92F and humidity levels of 75-85%. Salt air from the Atlantic Ocean and Intracoastal Waterway accelerates corrosion of outdoor AC units, particularly condenser coils and copper lines. The city\'s proximity to the ocean means AC systems run nearly year-round (March through November), making regular maintenance essential to prevent breakdowns during peak summer heat. Hurricane season (June-November) also requires HVAC systems to be in top condition. Professional service and corrosion protection are critical for extending system life in this coastal environment.'),
(1590,109,'neighborhoods','Victoria Park\nColee Hammock\nRio Vista\nPoinsettia Heights\nLauderdale Beach\nCoral Ridge\nImperial Point\nWilton Manors\nHarbor Beach\nLas Olas Isles\nSailboat Bend\nTarpon River\nBeverly Heights\nMelrose Park\nLauderdale Harbors\nSunrise Intracoastal\nMiddle River Terrace\nLauderdale-by-the-Sea\nPlantation Acres\nOakland Park'),
(1591,109,'service_area_note','<p><strong>Serving Fort Lauderdale Since 2005</strong></p>\n\n<p>We provide same-day HVAC service throughout Fort Lauderdale and surrounding areas. Our technicians are familiar with local building codes, permit requirements, and the specific HVAC challenges faced by Fort Lauderdale homeowners, including salt air corrosion and hurricane preparedness.</p>\n\n<p>Fast response times throughout Broward County. Emergency service available 24/7.</p>'),
(1592,109,'_service_area_note','field_city_service_area_note'),
(1593,118,'climate_note','Boca Raton\'s prestigious neighborhoods feature high-end homes with sophisticated HVAC systems, often including multi-zone climate control, advanced filtration, and smart home integration. The subtropical coastal climate demands year-round cooling, with summer temperatures of 88-92F and humidity averaging 75-80%. Salt air from the Atlantic Ocean and nearby Intracoastal Waterway can accelerate corrosion of outdoor units, particularly in waterfront communities. Luxury homes require specialized service from technicians experienced with premium brands like Carrier Infinity, Lennox Signature, and Trane XV systems. Professional maintenance preserves both comfort and property value in these exclusive communities.'),
(1594,118,'neighborhoods','Mizner Park\nRoyal Palm Polo\nThe Sanctuary\nBoca West\nBroken Sound\nSt. Andrews Country Club\nWoodfield Country Club\nBoca Pointe\nAddison Reserve\nThe Oaks\nBoca Falls\nBoca Bridges\nSpanish River\nPalmetto Pines\nDowntown Boca Raton\nBoca Raton Resort & Club\nTown Center\nOld Floresta\nLake Rogers Isles\nCamino Gardens'),
(1595,118,'service_area_note','<p><strong>Serving Boca Raton Since 2005</strong></p>\n\n<p>We provide premium HVAC service throughout Boca Raton\'s luxury communities and exclusive neighborhoods. Our technicians are factory-trained on high-end residential systems and familiar with the specific requirements of upscale homes, homeowners associations, and coastal properties.</p>\n\n<p>Same-day service available. Discretion and professionalism guaranteed for all estate properties.</p>'),
(1596,118,'_service_area_note','field_city_service_area_note'),
(1597,123,'climate_note','West Palm Beach\'s tropical climate brings intense heat and humidity year-round, with summer temperatures regularly reaching 90-94F and heat index values often exceeding 105F. As the largest city in Palm Beach County, it encompasses both coastal waterfront areas and inland neighborhoods, each with unique HVAC challenges. Salt air from the Intracoastal Waterway affects coastal properties, while inland areas experience even higher temperatures without ocean breezes. AC systems typically run 9-10 months per year (March through November), with peak demand during the summer months. Hurricane season requires reliable HVAC systems, and the combination of extreme heat and high humidity makes regular maintenance and prompt repairs essential for both residential and commercial properties.'),
(1598,123,'neighborhoods','Downtown West Palm Beach\nNorthwood\nFlamingo Park\nEl Cid\nOld Northwood Historic District\nSouth Olive\nWest Palm Beach Waterfront\nGrandview Heights\nLake Park\nNorthboro Park\nGeorgia Avenue District\nBelvedere Homes\nParker Avenue\nProspect Park\nForest Hill\nLake Worth Corridor\nPalm Beach Lakes\nWest Gate\nHaverhill\nLake Mangonia'),
(1599,123,'service_area_note','<p><strong>Serving West Palm Beach Since 2005</strong></p>\n\n<p>We provide comprehensive HVAC service throughout West Palm Beach and Palm Beach County. As the county seat and largest city in the area, we understand the diverse needs of residential, commercial, and historic properties. Our technicians are licensed, insured, and familiar with local building codes and permit requirements.</p>\n\n<p>24/7 emergency service available. Fast response times throughout the greater West Palm Beach area.</p>'),
(1600,123,'_service_area_note','field_city_service_area_note'),
(1601,112,'climate_note','Coral Springs\' inland location creates even hotter conditions than coastal areas, with summer temperatures often reaching 93-97F and heat index values exceeding 110F during peak summer months. Without the cooling ocean breeze, homes in this master-planned community rely heavily on air conditioning from March through November. The combination of extreme heat, afternoon thunderstorms, and humidity levels of 70-80% puts constant demand on HVAC systems. With predominantly single-family homes built from the 1970s onward, many properties have aging AC systems that require regular maintenance or replacement. Proper sizing, routine service, and prompt repairs are essential to avoid system failures during the hottest months when equipment works hardest.'),
(1602,112,'neighborhoods','Eagle Trace\nTurtle Run\nCoral Springs Country Club\nHeron Bay\nThe Woodlands\nRamblewood\nForest Hills\nCypress Run\nWhispering Woods\nCoral Shores\nWestchester\nEagle Glen\nCountry Glen\nRiverside\nCoral Ridge\nThe Ponds\nSawgrass Sanctuary\nParkland Isles\nRoyal Springs\nThe Meadows'),
(1603,112,'service_area_note','<p><strong>Serving Coral Springs Since 2005</strong></p>\n\n<p>We provide same-day HVAC service throughout Coral Springs\' residential communities and master-planned neighborhoods. Our technicians are familiar with the HVAC systems common in South Florida planned communities, from original 1970s-80s installations to modern high-efficiency systems.</p>\n\n<p>Fast response times throughout Broward County. Family-owned and locally operated.</p>'),
(1604,112,'_service_area_note','field_city_service_area_note'),
(1605,96,'climate_note','Pembroke Pines\' western inland location creates significantly hotter conditions than coastal communities, with summer temperatures frequently reaching 94-98F and heat index values often exceeding 110F. As the second most populous city in Broward County, it encompasses a wide range of residential neighborhoods from established 1960s-70s developments to newer construction. Without coastal breezes, homes rely on air conditioning up to 10 months per year. The combination of intense heat, high humidity (75-85%), and frequent afternoon thunderstorms puts tremendous strain on HVAC equipment. Many older homes have undersized or aging systems that struggle to keep up with South Florida\'s demanding climate. Regular maintenance, proper system sizing, and timely repairs are critical to maintaining comfort and avoiding costly emergency breakdowns.'),
(1606,96,'neighborhoods','Chapel Trail\nSilver Lakes\nPembroke Falls\nCentury Village\nPasadena Lakes\nSunset Lakes\nPembroke Isles\nGrand Palms\nThe Preserve\nTowngate\nHollybrook\nPembroke Lakes\nWaterways\nFlamingo West\nHampton Pines\nEmbassy Lakes\nPalm Lake Estates\nIsles at Pembroke Pines\nPine Tree Estates\nWestwood'),
(1607,96,'service_area_note','<p><strong>Serving Pembroke Pines Since 2005</strong></p>\n\n<p>We provide comprehensive HVAC service throughout Pembroke Pines, Broward County\'s second largest city. From Century Village to Chapel Trail, our technicians understand the diverse needs of both established and newer residential communities.</p>\n\n<p>Same-day service available. 24/7 emergency repairs for cooling system failures.</p>'),
(1608,96,'_service_area_note','field_city_service_area_note'),
(1609,102,'climate_note','Hollywood\'s prime coastal location between Miami and Fort Lauderdale brings beautiful Atlantic Ocean breezes but also significant HVAC challenges. Summer temperatures regularly reach 88-92F with humidity levels of 75-85%, while salt air from the ocean and Intracoastal Waterway accelerates corrosion of outdoor AC equipment. The city\'s beachfront properties, historic downtown, and residential neighborhoods all experience nearly year-round AC demands (March through November). The famous Hollywood Beach Boardwalk area and waterfront properties face particularly aggressive salt air corrosion of condenser coils and copper refrigerant lines. Hurricane season preparation is essential for maintaining reliable cooling systems. Regular maintenance with corrosion protection, timely repairs, and hurricane readiness are critical for both residential and commercial properties in this vibrant coastal community.'),
(1610,102,'neighborhoods','Hollywood Beach\nDowntown Hollywood\nHollywood Lakes\nEmerald Hills\nWest Hollywood\nHollywood Hills\nPark East\nPark Central\nCarver Ranches\nWashington Park\nLiberia\nOakridge\nLake Mabel\nDriftwood\nRoyal Poinciana\nThe Gardens\nHollywood Hills West\nAtlantic Shores\nDiplomat Parkway\nHillcrest'),
(1611,102,'service_area_note','<p><strong>Serving Hollywood Since 2005</strong></p>\n\n<p>We provide same-day HVAC service throughout Hollywood, from the iconic boardwalk to residential neighborhoods west of I-95. Our technicians specialize in coastal property HVAC challenges, including salt air corrosion protection and hurricane preparedness.</p>\n\n<p>24/7 emergency service available. Experienced with both residential and beachfront condo properties.</p>'),
(1612,102,'_service_area_note','field_city_service_area_note'),
(1613,95,'climate_note','Miramar\'s western inland location creates hotter conditions than coastal areas, with summer temperatures regularly reaching 92-96F and heat index values frequently exceeding 108F. As one of South Florida\'s fastest-growing cities, Miramar features a mix of established neighborhoods and newer developments with modern HVAC systems. Without ocean breezes, residents rely heavily on air conditioning 9-10 months per year (March through November). The combination of extreme heat, humidity levels of 75-80%, and rapid afternoon thunderstorms puts constant demand on cooling systems. Newer homes often feature high-efficiency AC systems, while older properties may have aging equipment that requires upgrading. Proper maintenance, timely repairs, and ensuring adequate system capacity are essential for maintaining comfort in this rapidly expanding community.'),
(1614,95,'neighborhoods','Miralago\nMonarch Lakes\nRiviera Isles\nSilver Shores\nParkland Preserve\nSunset Falls\nMiramar Isles\nVizcaya\nThe Hamptons\nPreserve at Miramar\nWelleby\nCaribbean Keys\nLandings\nHuntington\nFairway Estates\nCypress Lake\nEmbassy Lakes East\nPembroke Shores\nWest Miramar\nMiramar Pines'),
(1615,95,'service_area_note','<p><strong>Serving Miramar Since 2005</strong></p>\n\n<p>We provide same-day HVAC service throughout Miramar\'s growing residential communities. Our technicians are experienced with both newer high-efficiency systems and older equipment, ensuring quality service regardless of your home\'s age or system type.</p>\n\n<p>Fast response times throughout western Broward County. Family-owned and operated.</p>'),
(1616,95,'_service_area_note','field_city_service_area_note'),
(1617,114,'climate_note','Pompano Beach\'s coastal Atlantic location brings warm subtropical weather year-round, with summer temperatures reaching 88-92F and humidity levels of 75-85%. Salt air from the ocean accelerates corrosion of outdoor AC units, particularly affecting condenser coils and copper lines in beachfront and near-coastal properties. The city\'s mix of oceanfront condos, canal-front homes, and inland residential neighborhoods all experience nearly year-round cooling demands (March through November). The Pompano Beach Pier area and waterfront properties face especially aggressive salt air exposure. Hurricane season readiness and corrosion protection are essential considerations. AC systems in coastal Pompano Beach require more frequent maintenance than inland areas, with professional service, corrosion-resistant coatings, and timely repairs being critical for system longevity and reliability.'),
(1618,114,'neighborhoods','Pompano Beach Highlands\nCresthaven\nPalm-Aire\nLeisureville\nCollier Manor\nCypress Bend\nGardens at Pompano\nHillsboro Pines\nLakeside Green\nPompano Beach Waterways\nPompano Isles\nTerra Mar\nDunes of Pompano\nGardens of Pompano\nPompano Shores\nHammondville\nSanta Barbara Shores\nCrystal Lake\nTwin Lakes South\nBeach Central'),
(1619,114,'service_area_note','<p><strong>Serving Pompano Beach Since 2005</strong></p>\n\n<p>We provide same-day HVAC service throughout Pompano Beach, from oceanfront properties to inland communities. Our technicians specialize in coastal HVAC challenges, including salt air corrosion protection and humidity control for waterfront homes and condos.</p>\n\n<p>24/7 emergency service available. Experienced with coastal residential and high-rise properties.</p>'),
(1620,114,'_service_area_note','field_city_service_area_note'),
(1621,101,'climate_note','Davie\'s western inland location creates significantly hotter conditions than coastal areas, with summer temperatures often reaching 94-98F and heat index values routinely exceeding 110F. Known for its rural character, horse properties, and suburban neighborhoods, Davie features diverse housing from ranch-style homes to modern developments. Without ocean breezes, residents rely heavily on air conditioning 9-10 months per year (March through November). The combination of extreme heat, humidity levels of 75-85%, and frequent afternoon thunderstorms creates constant demand on HVAC systems. Properties with pole barns, workshops, or specialty cooling needs for animals require additional considerations. Western Broward\'s intense heat makes proper HVAC sizing, regular maintenance, and prompt repairs essential to avoid system failures during the hottest months.'),
