(1625,106,'climate_note','Plantation\'s central Broward location creates warm to hot conditions year-round, with summer temperatures regularly reaching 91-95F and heat index values often exceeding 105F. As an established city with many mature neighborhoods developed from the 1950s onward, Plantation features a mix of original homes with aging HVAC systems and updated properties with modern equipment. Without direct ocean breezes, residents rely on air conditioning 9-10 months per year (March through November). The combination of heat, humidity levels of 75-80%, and frequent afternoon storms puts steady demand on cooling systems. Many homes in older neighborhoods have HVAC systems nearing or past their expected 15-20 year lifespan. Regular maintenance, timely system upgrades, and professional repairs are essential for maintaining comfort in this well-established Broward community.'),
