(1722,97,'climate_note','South West Ranches\' western Broward location creates hot conditions year-round, with summer temperatures often reaching 94-98F and heat index values routinely exceeding 110F. Known for its rural character and large estate properties with horses, South West Ranches features unique HVAC needs including barn cooling, stable ventilation, and multi-zone residential systems. Without ocean breezes and with larger properties, homes rely heavily on air conditioning 9-10 months per year (March through November). Properties often require specialty cooling for animal facilities in addition to residential comfort. Professional maintenance, proper system sizing, and reliable repairs are essential for both homes and agricultural buildings in this equestrian community.'),
(1723,97,'neighborhoods','Rolling Oaks\nSouthwest Ranches Estates\nCountry Estates\nSunshine Ranches Border\nIvanhoe Estates\nLong Lake Ranches\nSilver Lakes Border\nRanch Colony\nStallion Acres\nEquestrian Estates\nGreen Meadows\nCountry Club Drive Area\nSouthwest 148th Avenue Area\nSouthwest 172nd Street Area\nGriffin Road Area\nStirling Road Area\nFlamingo Road Area\nRanch Estates\nSouth West Ranches Country Club\nLandmark Ranch Estates'),
(1724,97,'service_area_note','<p><strong>Serving South West Ranches Since 2005</strong></p>\n<p>We provide comprehensive HVAC service throughout South West Ranches, from residential homes to equestrian estates. Our technicians understand the unique needs of ranch properties with barns, stables, and specialty cooling requirements.</p>\n<p>Same-day service available. Experienced with estate properties and agricultural facilities.</p>'),
(1725,97,'_service_area_note','field_city_service_area_note'),
(1726,97,'zip_codes','33027\n33029\n33330\n33331\n33332'),
(1727,116,'climate_note','Lighthouse Point\'s coastal location brings warm subtropical weather year-round, with summer temperatures reaching 88-92F and humidity levels of 75-85%. Located between Pompano Beach and Deerfield Beach along the Intracoastal Waterway, this small waterfront community faces salt air exposure that accelerates corrosion of outdoor AC units. Canal-front homes and waterfront properties require specialized HVAC maintenance to combat coastal corrosion. AC systems in Lighthouse Point require more frequent maintenance than inland areas, with professional service, corrosion-resistant coatings, and timely repairs being critical for system longevity in this intimate waterfront community.'),
(1728,116,'neighborhoods','Lighthouse Point Marina Area\nIntracoastal Estates\nCanal Front Properties\nDan Witt Park Area\nFrank McDonough Park Area\nNortheast 24th Street Area\nLighthouse Point Yacht Club\nWaterfront Estates\nSample Road Area\nNorth Federal Highway\nLighthouse Point Boulevard\nNortheast 21st Court Area\nNortheast 28th Court Area\nHillsboro Canal Area\nEast Lighthouse Point\nWest Lighthouse Point\nCentral Lighthouse Point\nNorth Lighthouse Point\nSouth Lighthouse Point\nLighthouse Point Gardens'),
(1729,116,'service_area_note','<p><strong>Serving Lighthouse Point Since 2005</strong></p>\n<p>We provide same-day HVAC service throughout Lighthouse Point\'s waterfront community. Our technicians specialize in coastal HVAC challenges, including salt air corrosion protection for canal-front properties.</p>\n<p>24/7 emergency service. Experienced with waterfront and marina-area properties.</p>'),
(1730,116,'_service_area_note','field_city_service_area_note'),
(1731,116,'zip_codes','33064'),
(1732,104,'climate_note','Hialeah Lakes\' inland Miami-Dade location creates hot conditions year-round, with summer temperatures often reaching 92-96F and heat index values exceeding 108F. This small residential community features predominantly single-family homes that rely heavily on air conditioning 9-10 months per year (March through November). Without ocean breezes, the combination of extreme heat, humidity levels of 75-80%, and afternoon thunderstorms puts constant demand on HVAC systems. Regular maintenance, prompt repairs, and ensuring adequate system capacity are essential for maintaining comfort in this northern Miami-Dade community\'s demanding subtropical climate.'),
(1733,104,'neighborhoods','Lakes of the Meadow\nLake Lucerne\nCountry Lakes\nPalm Lakes\nMiami Lakes Border\nHialeah Border\nOpa-locka Border\nNorthwest 103rd Street Area\nNorthwest 107th Street Area\nNorthwest 109th Street Area\nEast Hialeah Lakes\nWest Hialeah Lakes\nCentral Hialeah Lakes\nNorth Hialeah Lakes\nSouth Hialeah Lakes\nHialeah Lakes Elementary Area\nGratigny Road Area\nNorthwest 87th Avenue Area\nNorthwest 97th Avenue Area\nHialeah Lakes Park Area'),
(1734,104,'service_area_note','<p><strong>Serving Hialeah Lakes Since 2005</strong></p>\n<p>We provide same-day HVAC service throughout Hialeah Lakes and northern Miami-Dade County. Our technicians are experienced with residential HVAC systems in small community settings.</p>\n<p>Fast response times. Emergency service available 24/7.</p>'),
(1735,104,'_service_area_note','field_city_service_area_note'),
(1736,104,'zip_codes','33014\n33018'),
(1737,167,'service_description','Regular AC maintenance is the key to keeping your air conditioning system running efficiently, preventing costly breakdowns, and extending the lifespan of your equipment. In South Florida\'s demanding climate where AC systems run nearly year-round, professional maintenance isn\'t optionalit\'s essential. Our comprehensive maintenance service includes thorough inspection, cleaning, testing, and tune-up of all system components to ensure peak performance and energy efficiency.\n\nDuring a maintenance visit, our certified technicians perform a detailed 20-point inspection covering everything from refrigerant levels and electrical connections to condensate drains and thermostat calibration. We clean or replace air filters, clean condenser and evaporator coils, check and tighten electrical connections, lubricate moving parts, test system controls, and verify proper airflow throughout your home.\n\nPreventative maintenance catches small issues before they become major problems, saves money on energy bills through improved efficiency, maintains manufacturer warranty requirements, and ensures your AC system is ready to handle Florida\'s brutal summer heat without failure.'),
(1738,167,'service_benefits_0_benefit','Lower Energy Bills Through Peak Efficiency'),
(1739,167,'_service_benefits_0_benefit','field_benefit_text'),
(1740,167,'service_benefits_1_benefit','Prevent Costly Emergency Repairs & Breakdowns'),
