(108,0,'2025-10-17 23:23:44','2025-10-17 23:23:44','Miami is South Florida\'s largest and most vibrant city, home to over 470,000 residents in the city proper and 2.7 million in the greater metropolitan area. The Magic City\'s diverse neighborhoods range from the gleaming high-rises of Brickell and Downtown to the colorful streets of Little Havana and the artistic enclaves of Wynwood and the Design District.\n\nMiami\'s tropical climate and rapid growth create unique HVAC challenges. The city\'s building stock includes everything from historic 1920s Mediterranean Revival homes in Coral Gables to ultra-modern luxury condominiums along Biscayne Bay. Each property type requires specialized HVAC knowledge and expertise.\n\nThe intense heat and humidity mean air conditioning isn\'t a luxuryit\'s a necessity. Miami residents run their AC systems nearly year-round, with peak usage from May through October when temperatures and humidity reach their highest levels. This constant demand requires reliable HVAC service from experienced local professionals who understand Miami\'s specific cooling needs.\n\nWhether you\'re in a waterfront condo dealing with salt air corrosion, a historic home requiring custom ductwork solutions, or a commercial property in the Design District needing efficient climate control, Sunnyside AC has the experience and expertise to keep your Miami property comfortable all year long.','Miami','','publish','closed','closed','','miami','','','2025-10-18 00:39:22','2025-10-18 00:39:22','',0,'https://sunnyside-ac.ddev.site/service-areas/miami-2/',0,'city','',0),
